@lipxu - Reviewed the latest version; no blockers from my side.

The root-cause explanation matches the code change: since the expected packet is the decapped inner packet, keeping the source PTF port in the expected egress set is valid and avoids false misses when LAG hashing selects that member. The per-packet success/failure recording also fixes the confusing `IndexError` path, and the new diagnostics are best-effort/budgeted so they should not affect healthy runs.

CI is green.

> Please make sure the extra overhead of this fixture doesn't increase test run times dramatically.

@prabhataravind 

No meaningful increase for passing runs, just one extra lightweight `show chassis module status` per test in platform_tests/. Extra time materializes only during actual DPU recovery or a rebooting DUT, both of which are necessary safety actions that improve suite reliability rather than slow down the happy path.

@aaronber0614 - could you add the **`Request for 202511 branch`** label to this PR so the cherry-pick bot backports it to `202511`?

Context: nightly is flagging `ssh.test_ssh_ciphers::test_ssh_enc_ciphers` on **Nokia-7215** (image 20251110, i.e. release **202511**) with the opaque `TypeError: Failed expected string ... got 'TIMEOUT'` -- exactly the `pytest.fail(e)` -> `pytest.fail(str(e))` (+ real-hostname prompt) fix in your `tests/ssh/test_ssh_ciphers.py` change here. I confirmed `202511` still has the pre-fix code (`pytest.fail(e)` + `duthost.hostname`), so the backport is needed.

Heads-up: `202511`'s `.azure-pipelines/pr_test_scripts.yaml` `t1-lag-vpp:` section differs from master, so a full cherry-pick of all 6 files may conflict there -- a targeted backport of just the `tests/ssh/test_ssh_ciphers.py` hunk would fully cover this. Happy to raise that manual cherry-pick if that's easier. Thanks!

